1
00:01:08,040 --> 00:01:09,992
[Episode 5:
I Dislike Black-Crowned Night Herons]

2
00:01:19,880 --> 00:01:21,750
Thanks. You're a lifesaver.

3
00:01:22,439 --> 00:01:23,763
You're welcome.

4
00:01:25,239 --> 00:01:26,799
You should've gotten mad.

5
00:01:26,799 --> 00:01:28,160
What?

6
00:01:28,160 --> 00:01:30,000
You should've passed the ball to me,

7
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:31,415
right?

8
00:01:36,240 --> 00:01:38,560
Do you know about
the black-crowned night heron?

9
00:01:38,560 --> 00:01:39,760
A bird that raises its crown

10
00:01:39,760 --> 00:01:41,565
when it encounters a predator.

11
00:01:42,239 --> 00:01:43,925
You should learn from it.

12
00:01:44,560 --> 00:01:46,480
I don't think I'm to blame.

13
00:01:46,480 --> 00:01:48,480
They enjoy bullying the weak.

14
00:01:48,480 --> 00:01:50,241
And I'm unfortunately targeted.

15
00:01:50,959 --> 00:01:53,069
It's just a friendly suggestion.

16
00:01:55,239 --> 00:01:57,199
I don't like black-crowned night herons.

17
00:01:58,560 --> 00:02:00,000
They're pretentious,

18
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:01,751
utterly hypocritical.

19
00:02:09,360 --> 00:02:11,110
30 cm.

20
00:02:21,320 --> 00:02:23,240
How dare you walk alone?

21
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:25,000
What about playing Street Fighter?

22
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:26,800
Good idea. It's been a while.

23
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:28,580
Where did you two get money?

24
00:02:34,160 --> 00:02:35,632
Alright.

25
00:02:43,439 --> 00:02:45,639
The sun is almost setting. Why the umbrella?

26
00:02:45,639 --> 00:02:47,436
Because I'm willing to.

27
00:02:50,240 --> 00:02:51,663
Hold this for me.

28
00:02:52,840 --> 00:02:55,360
Isn't this Xiang Nan Feng's notebook?

29
00:02:55,360 --> 00:02:57,280
Even a top student can be unmindful.

30
00:02:57,280 --> 00:02:59,517
I notice him secretly write something.

31
00:02:59,517 --> 00:03:00,812
I want to see!

32
00:03:01,440 --> 00:03:03,407
Does he look so careless?

33
00:03:10,480 --> 00:03:12,504
You go home first today.
I have something to do.

34
00:03:12,504 --> 00:03:14,000
What?

35
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:15,870
Where are you going?

36
00:03:16,600 --> 00:03:19,049
This road is all muddy.

37
00:03:20,680 --> 00:03:22,039
You're so cocky.

38
00:03:22,039 --> 00:03:24,727
I heard Street Fighter has a new character.

39
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:52,088
Xiang Nan Feng!

40
00:03:55,120 --> 00:03:57,699
Xiang Nan Feng!

41
00:04:04,480 --> 00:04:06,540
Xiang Nan Feng!

42
00:04:08,720 --> 00:04:10,330
Hurry up!

43
00:04:13,640 --> 00:04:15,016
Come on!

44
00:04:16,840 --> 00:04:18,346
Let's go!

45
00:04:25,360 --> 00:04:26,900
You're not going anywhere!

46
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:32,939
Come back!

47
00:04:43,480 --> 00:04:45,879
If you break it, you'll pay for it! Apologize!

48
00:04:45,879 --> 00:04:47,120
Who are you trying to scare?

49
00:04:47,120 --> 00:04:49,560
Try if you may. I...

50
00:04:49,560 --> 00:04:51,759
I'm not capable, but my dad is.

51
00:04:51,759 --> 00:04:53,680
If anything happens to me,

52
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:55,600
my dad will make you pay!

53
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:56,839
Chao, Chao!

54
00:04:56,839 --> 00:04:58,000
Her family is rich.

55
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:59,560
Maybe we should...

56
00:04:59,560 --> 00:05:01,012
Apologize!

57
00:05:07,454 --> 00:05:08,640
Sorry.

58
00:05:08,640 --> 00:05:10,399
- Never mind.
- Stop saying "Never mind".

59
00:05:10,399 --> 00:05:11,759
Whoever apologizes to you,

60
00:05:11,759 --> 00:05:13,800
you can refuse to forgive him.

61
00:05:13,800 --> 00:05:14,930
Only an idiot would blindly

62
00:05:14,930 --> 00:05:16,734
please others throughout his lifetime.

63
00:05:18,240 --> 00:05:19,360
You guys,

64
00:05:19,360 --> 00:05:20,571
which class are you in?

65
00:05:20,571 --> 00:05:22,880
- I sprained my ankle.
- What are you doing?

66
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:25,480
- Stop!
- Hey! You go first.

67
00:05:25,480 --> 00:05:26,480
I'll cover you.

68
00:05:26,480 --> 00:05:27,800
- Wait.
- Catch me.

69
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:29,480
What are you doing? Stop!

70
00:05:29,480 --> 00:05:31,120
- Hurry!
- Ren Xi Zhou!

71
00:05:31,120 --> 00:05:33,160
Why don't you tell me you can't ride?

72
00:05:33,160 --> 00:05:34,392
- I'm so mad!
- Which class?

73
00:05:34,392 --> 00:05:36,480
- Go!
- I thought it's easy.

74
00:05:36,480 --> 00:05:37,520
Hurry!

75
00:05:37,520 --> 00:05:39,639
- Run, idiot!
- Stop!

76
00:05:39,639 --> 00:05:41,490
That girl is pretty cool.

77
00:05:42,283 --> 00:05:44,702
Or rather, she's willful.

78
00:05:46,080 --> 00:05:48,515
Then what? Were they caught?

79
00:05:51,480 --> 00:05:52,880
<i>Thanks for your help.</i>

80
00:05:52,880 --> 00:05:54,779
<i>Let's have dinner tomorrow night.</i>

81
00:05:59,840 --> 00:06:00,920
Take your time.

82
00:06:00,920 --> 00:06:02,348
I'll take care of the store.

83
00:06:05,040 --> 00:06:08,546
[Are you still mad about that day?]

84
00:06:26,480 --> 00:06:27,920
<i>Are you still mad about that day?</i>

85
00:06:27,920 --> 00:06:29,773
<i>I don't want to talk to you.</i>

86
00:06:53,120 --> 00:06:54,395
<i>Okay.</i>

87
00:07:29,720 --> 00:07:31,646
What am I doing?

88
00:07:32,639 --> 00:07:35,238
Just a meal with a colleague.

89
00:07:46,759 --> 00:07:48,240
Hello?

90
00:07:48,240 --> 00:07:50,665
My pal's ex asked him out for dinner.

91
00:07:53,280 --> 00:07:54,597
Say something.

92
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:57,552
Say something!

93
00:08:00,254 --> 00:08:01,560
Where are you?

94
00:08:01,560 --> 00:08:02,986
Speak up!

95
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:07,322
Here, here, here.

96
00:08:08,120 --> 00:08:09,872
What's up?

97
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:17,125
Isn't it a date?

98
00:08:17,125 --> 00:08:19,141
- Work.
- Date!

99
00:08:19,141 --> 00:08:20,932
Work.

100
00:08:22,385 --> 00:08:23,760
Alright.

101
00:08:23,760 --> 00:08:25,160
What does your pal wonder?

102
00:08:25,160 --> 00:08:26,680
How to win back his ex

103
00:08:26,680 --> 00:08:28,058
during dinner?

104
00:08:28,760 --> 00:08:30,225
No chance.

105
00:08:31,160 --> 00:08:32,512
Why?

106
00:08:34,120 --> 00:08:35,600
When an ex invites,

107
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:38,080
if you accept, you seem too eager;

108
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:40,160
if you refuse, you seem to be not over it.

109
00:08:40,160 --> 00:08:41,440
Being not sober yet,

110
00:08:41,440 --> 00:08:43,080
he ponders how to win.

111
00:08:43,080 --> 00:08:44,680
Overthinking is the worst.

112
00:08:44,680 --> 00:08:46,160
The more you think, the more you care.

113
00:08:46,160 --> 00:08:47,840
Who cares, who loses.

114
00:08:47,840 --> 00:08:49,370
He doesn't care.

115
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:53,645
He said so.

116
00:08:55,920 --> 00:08:57,439
How about this?

117
00:08:59,360 --> 00:09:00,679
He's neither so serious

118
00:09:00,679 --> 00:09:02,960
as to look expecting,

119
00:09:02,960 --> 00:09:04,559
nor so casual

120
00:09:04,559 --> 00:09:06,755
as to look indifferent.

121
00:09:08,759 --> 00:09:09,879
He'd better be

122
00:09:09,879 --> 00:09:11,879
refined but slightly casual,

123
00:09:11,879 --> 00:09:14,639
casual but slightly refined.

124
00:09:14,639 --> 00:09:16,972
So that she can't tell.

125
00:09:19,018 --> 00:09:21,240
If he ponders about his ex, he loses.

126
00:09:21,240 --> 00:09:22,814
If his ex ponders about him,

127
00:09:22,814 --> 00:09:24,559
he wins!

128
00:09:26,520 --> 00:09:28,156
Remember:

129
00:09:28,156 --> 00:09:30,210
Who looks eager,

130
00:09:30,210 --> 00:09:32,155
who's the loser.

131
00:09:41,480 --> 00:09:43,350
[Let Go Yard]

132
00:09:44,120 --> 00:09:45,465
Let's go.

133
00:09:52,480 --> 00:09:54,704
You can't ride a bike, can you?

134
00:09:54,704 --> 00:09:56,440
I have an electric motorcycle.

135
00:09:56,440 --> 00:09:58,720
My three-wheeler is faster.

136
00:09:58,720 --> 00:10:00,018
Hop on.

137
00:10:16,400 --> 00:10:19,226
Sit tight. Don't fall off later.

138
00:10:37,840 --> 00:10:39,200
Look, he's so funny.

139
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:40,559
Isn't he silly?

140
00:10:40,559 --> 00:10:43,040
Can't even take a three-wheeler.

141
00:10:43,040 --> 00:10:44,495
Let's go.

142
00:10:49,687 --> 00:10:51,003
[Qiuping Diner Specialties]

143
00:10:51,003 --> 00:10:52,400
Enjoy your meal.

144
00:10:52,400 --> 00:10:53,560
[Qiuping Diner]
Here, please wait.

145
00:10:53,560 --> 00:10:55,276
Hurry up!

146
00:10:57,160 --> 00:10:58,850
Please sit here.

147
00:10:59,720 --> 00:11:01,480
- Hurry up!
- Soon.

148
00:11:01,480 --> 00:11:03,160
Sir, are you in a hurry to eat?

149
00:11:03,160 --> 00:11:04,600
Next!

150
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:06,080
I'm sorry.

151
00:11:06,080 --> 00:11:07,799
- Enjoy your meal.
- Ren Xi Zhou.

152
00:11:07,799 --> 00:11:10,559
Please keep 30 cm from me.

153
00:11:10,559 --> 00:11:11,680
Okay, Mr. Xiang.

154
00:11:11,680 --> 00:11:13,141
This way.

155
00:11:15,080 --> 00:11:16,679
Enjoy, enjoy.

156
00:11:16,679 --> 00:11:18,993
Please move forward.

157
00:11:19,760 --> 00:11:21,374
Here's your food.

158
00:11:22,160 --> 00:11:23,600
What's going on?

159
00:11:23,600 --> 00:11:25,200
They're waiting! Hurry up!

160
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:26,844
Soon!

161
00:11:27,566 --> 00:11:29,360
- Take it.
- Stop dawdling!

162
00:11:29,360 --> 00:11:31,654
- They're waiting. Hurry!
- 30 cm.

163
00:11:32,680 --> 00:11:34,200
Hurry, hurry!

164
00:11:34,945 --> 00:11:35,970
Hold on, hold on.

165
00:11:35,970 --> 00:11:37,069
[Qiuping Diner Specialties]

166
00:11:41,840 --> 00:11:43,629
Perhaps we can...

167
00:11:43,629 --> 00:11:45,407
share?

168
00:11:52,880 --> 00:11:54,868
30 cm.

169
00:11:57,040 --> 00:11:58,994
<i>30 cm.</i>

170
00:12:02,480 --> 00:12:03,840
No need when dining.

171
00:12:03,840 --> 00:12:05,360
- How about cooking?
- No need.

172
00:12:05,360 --> 00:12:06,480
Three-legged race?

173
00:12:06,480 --> 00:12:07,872
No need.

174
00:12:10,080 --> 00:12:12,200
Have a three-legged race with you?

175
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:13,974
Just in case.

176
00:12:28,160 --> 00:12:29,706
Let's eat.

177
00:12:38,920 --> 00:12:41,200
The fried fish skin is so crispy!

178
00:12:41,200 --> 00:12:43,372
I think it's coated with batter and pan-fried.

179
00:12:46,452 --> 00:12:48,680
It's stewed so tenderly.
The fat melts in your mouth.

180
00:12:48,680 --> 00:12:50,200
If you add kiwi to a stew,

181
00:12:50,200 --> 00:12:51,679
it gets softer.

182
00:12:51,679 --> 00:12:52,680
Why?

183
00:12:52,680 --> 00:12:54,704
No reason.
